Adjust racks to middle and top positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}.

== Roasted Potatoes ==

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon}, @dried thyme{1%teaspoon}, and a big pinch of @salt and @pepper.

Roast on middle rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Cherry Balsamic Chicken ==

While potatoes roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt and @pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least ~{5%minutes}.

> Swap in pork or beef for chicken. Cook pork until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side; or cook beef to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

== Roasted Broccoli ==

While chicken cooks, toss broccoli on a second baking sheet with a large drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Cherry Balsamic Sauce ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add shallot; cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%teaspoon}; simmer until slightly reduced, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Add @cherry jam{1}, @water{1/3%cup}. Cook until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt, @pepper, and up to @sugar{1/2%teaspoon} to taste.

Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

Return chicken to pan; turn to coat in sauce.

== To Serve ==

> We kept the sides simple to allow the meat and sauce to shine. And boy, do they steal the show.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Top chicken with any remaining sauce and serve.